slaMonitorMib.name: slaMonitorMib

revisions.description: Version 5: Added support for remote NTR and RTP test initiation and results retrieval using SNMP. Defined attribute to support refusing server test requests.
Version 4: Added slaMonitorAgentServerBypass and updated conformance statements for cross-platform use.
Version 3: Added slaMonitorAgentCertFileInstallAction, slaMonitorAgentCertFile for VSP9K/ERS8800
Version 2: Added slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentVrfName, slaMonitorAgentSlaParameter for VSP9K
Version 1: Initial version. Basic agent support.

slaMonitorMib.contactinfo: John Seligson Avaya Networks, Inc. 4655 Great America Parkway Santa Clara, CA 95054 USA Phone: +1 408 496 3424 Email: jseligso@avaya.com
slaMonitorMib.description: An Avaya management module containing data definitions related to the SLA Monitor Agent.

slaMonitorAgentStatus.name: slaMonitorAgentStatus
slaMonitorAgentStatus.description: The value of this attribute indicates whether the SLA Monitor agent is enabled or not. An agent that is enabled will respond to SLA Monitor server discovery packets. A disabled agent will remain dormant until manually enabled.

slaMonitorAgentAddressType.name: slaMonitorAgentAddressType
slaMonitorAgentAddressType.description: The type of IP address used by the agent. This object is limited to IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

slaMonitorAgentAddress.name: slaMonitorAgentAddress
slaMonitorAgentAddress.description: The IP address currently used by the SLA Monitor agent.

slaMonitorAgentPort.name: slaMonitorAgentPort
slaMonitorAgentPort.description: The UDP port currently used by the SLA Monitor agent for agent-server communication.

slaMonitorAgentRegisteredWithServer.name: slaMonitorAgentRegisteredWithServer
slaMonitorAgentRegisteredWithServer.description: The value of this attribute indicates whether the SLA Monitor agent is registered with an SLA Monitor server or not.

slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddrType.name: slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddrType
slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddrType.description: The type of IP address used by the server. This object is limited to IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddr.name: slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddr
slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerAddr.description: The IP address of the SLA Monitor server with which the agent is currently registered.

slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerPort.name: slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerPort
slaMonitorAgentRegisteredServerPort.description: The TCP port utilized by the SLA Monitor server with which the agent is currently registered.

slaMonitorAgentRegistrationTime.name: slaMonitorAgentRegistrationTime
slaMonitorAgentRegistrationTime.description: Specifies the maximum amount of time, in seconds, until the current registration period expires.

slaMonitorAgentCliAvailable.name: slaMonitorAgentCliAvailable
slaMonitorAgentCliAvailable.description: The value of this attribute indicates whether the SLA Monitor agent CLI is available or not.

slaMonitorAgentCliTimeout.name: slaMonitorAgentCliTimeout
slaMonitorAgentCliTimeout.description: Specifies the maximum amount of time, in seconds, until the CLI session is automatically terminated. The value of this attribute is pertinent only if CLI timeouts are enabled (slaMonitorAgentCliTimeoutMode equals 'enable(1)').

slaMonitorAgentCliTimeoutMode.name: slaMonitorAgentCliTimeoutMode
slaMonitorAgentCliTimeoutMode.description: The value of this attribute indicates whether the SLA Monitor agent automatic CLI session timeout is enabled or not. When this attribute is set to 'enable(1)', a CLI session will automatically timeout after slaMonitorAgentCliTimeout seconds.

slaMonitorAgentSupportedApps.name: slaMonitorAgentSupportedApps
slaMonitorAgentSupportedApps.description: An enumeration of the SLA Monitor agent capabilities.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddrType.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddrType
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddrType.description: The type of IP address used by the agent. This object is limited to IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddr.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddr
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddr.description: The IP address of the SLA Monitor agent. If the value of this attribute is 0.0.0.0, the SLA Monitor agent will utilize an active device IP address by default.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentPort.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentPort
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentPort.description: The UDP port utilized by the SLA Monitor agent for agent-server communication. If the value of this attribute is zero, the SLA Monitor agent will utilize a default port value for communication purposes.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddrType.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddrType
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddrType.description: The type of IP address used by the server. This object is limited to IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddr.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddr
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddr.description: The IP address of the SLA Monitor server with which the agent is allowed to register. If the value of this attribute is not 0.0.0.0, the SLA Monitor agent may only respond to server requests originating at the specified IP address (or the IP address specified by the slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddr object if it is non-zero).

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerPort.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerPort
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerPort.description: The TCP port utilized by the SLA Monitor server with which the agent is allowed to register. If the value of this attribute is non-zero, the SLA Monitor agent may only respond to server requests originating from the specified port (or from the port specified by the slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerPort object if it is non-zero).

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddrTy.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddrType
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddrTy.description: The type of IP address used by the server. This object is limited to IPv4 and IPv6 addresses.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddr.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddr
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerAddr.description: The IP address of the alternate SLA Monitor server with which the agent is allowed to register. If the value of this attribute is not 0.0.0.0, the SLA Monitor agent may only respond to server requests originating at the specified IP address (or the IP address specified by the slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerAddr object if it is non-zero).

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerPort.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerPort
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAltServerPort.description: The TCP port utilized by the alternate SLA Monitor server with which the agent is allowed to register. If the value of this attribute is non-zero, the SLA Monitor agent may only respond to server requests originating from the specified port (or from the port specified by the slaMonitorAgentConfiguredServerPort object if it is non-zero).

slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort.name: slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort
slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort.description: The base UDP port currently used by the SLA Monitor agent for agent-agent communication. The base UDP port is used to derive multiple agent communication ports. An even base port values causes slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort and slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort+1 ports to be used. An odd base port values causes slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort and slaMonitorAgentToAgentPort-1 ports to be used.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentToAgentPor.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentToAgentPort
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentToAgentPor.description: The UDP port utilized by the SLA Monitor agent for agent-agent communication. If the value of this attribute is zero, the SLA Monitor agent will utilize a default port value for the base agent-agent UDP communication port.

slaMonitorAgentEncryptionSupport.name: slaMonitorAgentEncryptionSupport
slaMonitorAgentEncryptionSupport.description: Specifies if encrypted agent-server communication is supported by the agent.

slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentVrfName.name: slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentVrfName
slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentVrfName.description: The name of the virtual Router which SLA Monitor Agent IP address (slaMonitorAgentConfiguredAgentAddr) is associated with. This is only supported on VSP9K for now

slaMonitorAgentSlaParameter.name: slaMonitorAgentSlaParameter
slaMonitorAgentSlaParameter.description: String directly passed to the SLA Agent as parameter

slaMonitorAgentCertFileInstallAction.name: slaMonitorAgentCertFileInstallAction
slaMonitorAgentCertFileInstallAction.description: Operation object to install and deinstall the certificate file to a platform specific location. 'noactio' -is default setting and always is returned when this object is queried. 'install', object slaMonitorAgentCertFile will be used as source certificate file to install . 'deinstall', will ignore object slaMonitorAgentCertFile and just deinstall or remove the certificate file from the installed location

slaMonitorAgentCertFile.name: slaMonitorAgentCertFile
slaMonitorAgentCertFile.description: the certification file name for installation. It is only valid or used when object slaMonitorAgentCertFileInstallAction is set to install. Otherwise, it will be ignored

slaMonitorAgentServerBypass.name: slaMonitorAgentServerBypass
slaMonitorAgentServerBypass.description: The value of this attribute determines whether the SLA Monitor agent can perform certain operations without being registered with a server. When this attribute is set to 'enable(1)', an agent will respond to agent-to-agent test requests regardless of the server registration status. A 'disable(2)' setting will restrict agent responses when the agent is not registered with an SLA Monitor server.

slaMonitorAgentRefuseServerTests.name: slaMonitorAgentRefuseServerTests
slaMonitorAgentRefuseServerTests.description: The value of this attribute determines whether the SLA Monitor agent will refuse test requests from the server. When this attribute is set to 'allow(1)', an agent will accept test requests from the server. A 'refuse(2)' setting will cause the agent to reject test requests from the server. From a usage perspective, it may be necessary to temporarily refuse server test requests if the agent is being actively managed by a server but the administrator wishes to use the CLI or SNMP interfaces to initiate tests manually.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable
slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable.description: Defines the SLAMon agent NTR test control table supporting the ability to initiate NTR tests remotely. The results of NTR test operations are stored in the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable and the slaMonitorNtrHopsTable.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry
slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable. The first index element, slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId, is of type SnmpAdminString, allowing for a management application to identify its entries. The second index, slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName (also an SnmpAdminString), enables the same management application to have multiple requests configured.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId
slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId.description: The owner of an NTR test.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName
slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName.description: The name of an NTR test. This value is locally unique, within the scope of an slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlTargetAddress.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlTargetAddress
slaMonitorNtrCtrlTargetAddress.description: Specifies the target address used for the NTR test. The address type can be determined by examining the value of the corresponding slaMonitorNtrCtrlTargetAddressType. A value for this object MUST be provided during entry creation.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlDscp.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlDscp
slaMonitorNtrCtrlDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value for use in packets that are generated by the NTR test.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlAttempts.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlAttempts
slaMonitorNtrCtrlAttempts.description: Specifies the number of attempts are generated by the NTR test.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlPeriod.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlPeriod
slaMonitorNtrCtrlPeriod.description: Specifies the interval between packets, in microseconds, generated by the NTR test.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus
slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus.description: Used to initiate an NTR test: enabled(1) - initiate the test as defined by this slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry. disabled(2) - deactivate the test defined by this slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry, if possible. Refer to the corresponding slaMonitorNtrResultsOperStatus to determine the operational state of the test defined by this entry. When queried, 'disabled(2)' is always returned for this attribute.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlLabel.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlLabel
slaMonitorNtrCtrlLabel.description: A label used to reference the NTR control entry in a textual manner.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlStorageType.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlStorageType
slaMonitorNtrCtrlStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row.

slaMonitorNtrCtrlRowStatus.name: slaMonitorNtrCtrlRowStatus
slaMonitorNtrCtrlRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable. Deletion of an entry in this table results in the deletion of all corresponding (i.e., entries with the same slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId and slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName index values) entries in the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable and the slaMonitorNtrHopsTable. Initiation of an NTR test corresponding to this entry is controlled via slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus and not by entry creation. The operational state of an NTR test can be determined by examining the corresponding slaMonitorNtrResultsOperStatus object.

slaMonitorNtrResultsTable.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsTable
slaMonitorNtrResultsTable.description: Defines the SLAMon agent NTR results table that is used to track the status of NTR tests initiated through the the slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable. An entry is added to the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable when an NTR test defined by an slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry is started by transition of its slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus object to 'enabled(1)'. If the object slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus has the value 'disabled(2)', then successfully writing 'enabled(1)' to the object slaMonitorNtrCtrlAdminStatus re-initializes an already existing entry in the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable. The values of objects in the re-initialized entry are the same as the values of objects in a new entry would be. An entry is removed from the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable when its corresponding slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry is deleted.

slaMonitorNtrResultsEntry.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsEntry
slaMonitorNtrResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the slaMonitorNtrResultsTable. The slaMonitorNtrResultsTable has the same indexing as the slaMonitorNtrCtrlTable so that a slaMonitorNtrResultsEntry corresponds to the slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry that caused it to be created.

slaMonitorNtrResultsOperStatus.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsOperStatus
slaMonitorNtrResultsOperStatus.description: Reflects the operational state of an slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry: inProgress(1) - test is active. aborted(2) - test has been stopped. Refer to object slaMonitorNtrResultsAbortData for details. completed(3) - test is completed. Refer to objects slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionData and slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionSummary for details.

slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddressType.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddressType
slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of the source IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddress.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddress
slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcAddress.description: Specifies the source IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddressType.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddressType
slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of the destination IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddress.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddress
slaMonitorNtrResultsDstAddress.description: Specifies the destination IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcPort.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcPort
slaMonitorNtrResultsSrcPort.description: Specifies the Layer 4 source port used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsDstPort.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsDstPort
slaMonitorNtrResultsDstPort.description: Specifies the Layer 4 destination port used for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsDscp.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsDscp
slaMonitorNtrResultsDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value contained in NTR test packets generated by the agent for this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsTTL.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsTTL
slaMonitorNtrResultsTTL.description: The maximum time-to-live (TTL) value used during the execution of this test.

slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionData.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionData
slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionData.description: Provides details related to test completion. Multiple bits may be set to convey test status.

slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionSummary.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionSummary
slaMonitorNtrResultsCompletionSummary.description: A user-readable string that is used to convey test results for completed tests in an easy-to-understand format.

slaMonitorNtrResultsAbortData.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsAbortData
slaMonitorNtrResultsAbortData.description: Provides details for tests that were aborted. Multiple bits may be set to convey test status.

slaMonitorNtrResultsHopCount.name: slaMonitorNtrResultsHopCount
slaMonitorNtrResultsHopCount.description: The total number of hops for which information has been acquired during the execution of this test.

slaMonitorNtrHopsTable.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsTable
slaMonitorNtrHopsTable.description: Defines the SLAMon agent NTR test hop table for keeping track of the results of NTR tests on a per-hop basis.

slaMonitorNtrHopsEntry.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsEntry
slaMonitorNtrHopsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the slaMonitorNtrHopsTable. The first two index elements identify the slaMonitorNtrCtrlEntry with which this slaMonitorNtrHopsEntry is associated. The third index element, slaMonitorNtrHopsHopIndex, selects a hop in an NTR test path.

slaMonitorNtrHopsHopIndex.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsHopIndex
slaMonitorNtrHopsHopIndex.description: Specifies the hop index for an NTR test hop. Values for this object with respect to the same slaMonitorNtrCtrlOwnerId and slaMonitorNtrCtrlTestName MUST start at 1 and be given increasing values for subsequent hops. The value of slaMonitorNtrHopsHopIndex does not necessarily represent the number of the hop on the traced path, though this is normally the case.

slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddressType.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddressType
slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of address stored in the corresponding slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddress object.

slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddress.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddress
slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddress.description: This object reports the IP address associated with the NTR test hop.

slaMonitorNtrHopsRtt.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsRtt
slaMonitorNtrHopsRtt.description: The NTR test round-trip-time (RTT), in microseconds, computed for this hop.

slaMonitorNtrHopsIngressDscp.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsIngressDscp
slaMonitorNtrHopsIngressDscp.description: The DSCP value in the NTR test packet received by the target host (slaMonitorNtrHopsTgtAddress) for this hop.

slaMonitorNtrHopsEgressDscp.name: slaMonitorNtrHopsEgressDscp
slaMonitorNtrHopsEgressDscp.description: The DSCP value in the NTR test response packet received by the SLAMon agent for this hop.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable
slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable.description: Defines the SLAMon agent RTP test control table supporting the ability to initiate RTP tests remotely. The results of RTP test operations are stored in the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry
slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable. The first index element, slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId, is of type SnmpAdminString, allowing for a management application to identify its entries. The second index, slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestName (also an SnmpAdminString), enables the same management application to have multiple requests configured.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId
slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId.description: The owner of an RTP test.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestName.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestName
slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestName.description: The name of an RTP test. This is locally unique, within the scope of an slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlTargetAddress.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlTargetAddress
slaMonitorRtpCtrlTargetAddress.description: Specifies the target address used for the RTP test. The address type can be determined by examining the value of the corresponding slaMonitorRtpCtrlTargetAddressType. A value for this object MUST be provided during entry creation.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlDscp.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlDscp
slaMonitorRtpCtrlDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value for use in packets that are generated by the RTP test.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestPackets.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestPackets
slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestPackets.description: Specifies the number of test packets that are generated by the RTP test. Test packets are used for jitter determination.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlSyncPackets.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlSyncPackets
slaMonitorRtpCtrlSyncPackets.description: Specifies the number of synchronization packets that are generated by the RTP test. Sync packets are used for network delay determination.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlPeriod.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlPeriod
slaMonitorRtpCtrlPeriod.description: Specifies the interval between packets (in microseconds) generated by the RTP test.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus
slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus.description: Used to initiate an RTP test: enabled(1) - initiate the test as defined by this slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry. disabled(2) - deactivate the test defined by this slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry, if possible. Refer to the corresponding slaMonitorRtpResultsOperStatus to determine the operational state of the test defined by this entry. When queried, 'disabled(2)' is always returned for this attribute.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlLabel.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlLabel
slaMonitorRtpCtrlLabel.description: A label used to reference the RTP control entry in a textual manner.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlStorageType.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlStorageType
slaMonitorRtpCtrlStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row.

slaMonitorRtpCtrlRowStatus.name: slaMonitorRtpCtrlRowStatus
slaMonitorRtpCtrlRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable. Deletion of an entry in this table results in the deletion of all corresponding (i.e., entries with the same slaMonitorRtpCtrlOwnerId and slaMonitorRtpCtrlTestName index values) entries in the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable. Initiation of an RTP test corresponding to this entry is controlled via slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus and not by entry creation. The operational state of an RTP test can be determined by examining the corresponding slaMonitorRtpResultsOperStatus object.

slaMonitorRtpResultsTable.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsTable
slaMonitorRtpResultsTable.description: Defines the SLAMon agent RTP results table that is used to track the status of RTP tests initiated through the the slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable. An entry is added to the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable when an RTP test defined by an slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry is started by transition of its slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus object to 'enabled(1)'. If the object slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus has the value 'disabled(2)', then successfully writing 'enabled(1)' to the object slaMonitorRtpCtrlAdminStatus re-initializes an already existing entry in the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable. The values of objects in the re-initialized entry are the same as the values of objects in a new entry would be. An entry is removed from the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable when its corresponding slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry is deleted.

slaMonitorRtpResultsEntry.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsEntry
slaMonitorRtpResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the slaMonitorRtpResultsTable. The slaMonitorRtpResultsTable has the same indexing as the slaMonitorRtpCtrlTable so that a slaMonitorRtpResultsEntry corresponds to the slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry that caused it to be created.

slaMonitorRtpResultsOperStatus.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsOperStatus
slaMonitorRtpResultsOperStatus.description: Reflects the operational state of an slaMonitorRtpCtrlEntry: inProgress(1) - test is active. aborted(2) - test has been stopped. Refer to object slaMonitorRtpResultsAbortData for details. completed(3) - test is completed. Refer to objects that contain completed test results (all attributes except slaMonitorRtpResultsAbortData) for details.

slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddressType.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddressType
slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of the source IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddress.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddress
slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcAddress.description: Specifies the source IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddressType.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddressType
slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of the destination IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddress.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddress
slaMonitorRtpResultsDstAddress.description: Specifies the destination IP address used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcPort.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcPort
slaMonitorRtpResultsSrcPort.description: Specifies the Layer 4 source port used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsDstPort.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsDstPort
slaMonitorRtpResultsDstPort.description: Specifies the Layer 4 destination port used for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsDscp.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsDscp
slaMonitorRtpResultsDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value contained in RTP test packets generated by the agent for this test.

slaMonitorRtpResultsAverageDelay.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsAverageDelay
slaMonitorRtpResultsAverageDelay.description: The average network delay (RTT) experienced during this test sequence, in microseconds.

slaMonitorRtpResultsMedianDelay.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsMedianDelay
slaMonitorRtpResultsMedianDelay.description: The median network delay (RTT) experienced during this test sequence, in microseconds.

slaMonitorRtpResultsPacketLoss.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsPacketLoss
slaMonitorRtpResultsPacketLoss.description: A count of packets lost during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsOutOfOrderArrivals.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsOutOfOrderArrivals
slaMonitorRtpResultsOutOfOrderArrivals.description: The number of out-of-order arrivals detected during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile0.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile0
slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile0.description: The quartile 0 network jitter value, in microseconds, experienced during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile1.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile1
slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile1.description: The quartile 1 network jitter value, in microseconds, experienced during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile2.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile2
slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile2.description: The quartile 2 network jitter value, in microseconds, experienced during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile3.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile3
slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile3.description: The quartile 3 network jitter value, in microseconds, experienced during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile4.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile4
slaMonitorRtpResultsJitterQuartile4.description: The quartile 4 network jitter value, in microseconds, experienced during this test sequence.

slaMonitorRtpResultsAbortData.name: slaMonitorRtpResultsAbortData
slaMonitorRtpResultsAbortData.description: Provides details for tests that were aborted. Multiple bits may be set to convey test status.

slaMonitorAgentExceptionDetected.name: slaMonitorAgentExceptionDetected
slaMonitorAgentExceptionDetected.description: Indicates that an exception event that impacts the local SLA Monitor agent has been detected.

slaMonitorMibCompliance.name: slaMonitorMibCompliance
slaMonitorMibCompliance.description: Describes the requirements for conformance to the Avaya Networks SLA Monitor Agent MIB.

slaMonitorAgentConfigGroup.name: slaMonitorAgentConfigGroup
slaMonitorAgentConfigGroup.description: Objects used for SLA Monitor Agent configuration and monitoring.

slaMonitorAgentNtrTestGroup.name: slaMonitorAgentNtrTestGroup
slaMonitorAgentNtrTestGroup.description: Objects used for SLA Monitor Agent NTR test execution and results reporting.

slaMonitorAgentRtpTestGroup.name: slaMonitorAgentRtpTestGroup
slaMonitorAgentRtpTestGroup.description: Objects used for SLA Monitor Agent RTP test execution and results reporting.
